The paper proposes a novel approach for learning a classifier with control on the false-positive rate, which is a common problem in machine learning applications. The paper discusses the efficiency of the proposed approach and provides theoretical analysis and experimental results to support its superiority over existing approaches. Based on this, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
